We are trying to use pathplanner for a path during auton which starts facing the alliance wall (180 degrees). However I see on SmartDashBoard that PathPlanner is updating my swerveDrivePoseEstimator’s odemeter but it is not updating the gyro to make it 180 degree but instead leaving it at 0 making my controls inverted during teleop. We have competition on Friday and it would be SUPER useful if someone could help us out!!</p>
<p>Here is the swervesubsystem in my code: <a href="https://github.com/Royal-Robotics-5842/5842FRC_2025/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/SwerveSubsystem.java" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">5842FRC_2025/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/SwerveSubsystem.java at main · Royal-Robotics-5842/5842FRC_2025 · GitHub</a></p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-13T04:20:40.370Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":21,"reads":59,"readers_count":58,"score":116.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":495413,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-heading-issue","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/Royal-Robotics-5842/5842FRC_2025/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/SwerveSubsystem.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"5842FRC_2025/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/SwerveSubsystem.java at main · Royal-Robotics-5842/5842FRC_2025 · GitHub","clicks":4}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":65426,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-heading-issue/495413/1","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3555876,"name":"Dylan Powers","username":"Dylan1259","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dylan1259/{size}/161876_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-13T04:39:13.324Z","cooked":"<p>Taking a cursory look, it seems like PathPlanner doesn’t touch your gyro at all, so you will have to do that manually. Something along the lines of grabbing the initial heading from the PathPlanner path and applying it to your gyro upon initialization.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-13T04:39:20.262Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":53,"readers_count":52,"score":15.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":495413,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-heading-issue","display_username":"Dylan Powers","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":42126,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-heading-issue/495413/2","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3555939,"name":"","username":"RoyalKnight","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ce7236/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-13T09:48:36.089Z","cooked":"<p>Thank you so much! I kind of realized this as well but I’m not really sure if that’s what I should do as in hard coding it… Is that what you guys do?</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-13T09:51:50.891Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":38,"readers_count":37,"score":17.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":495413,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-heading-issue","display_username"